  p_ResponseFormat_ec79d5fa := 'JSON';
  p_MinPowerRank_ec79d5fa := 0;
  p_SelectionStrategy_ec79d5fa := 'Specific';
  p_PowerPreference_ec79d5fa := 'Highest';
  p_ParallelizationMode_ec79d5fa := 'None';
  p_OutputType_ec79d5fa := 'object';
  p_OutputExample_ec79d5fa := '{"description":"Planning Designer Agent has two modes: Creation (writes TechnicalDesign) and Modification (writes modificationPlan). Always set taskComplete: true and write output via payloadChangeRequest.","example_1_creation_mode":{"taskComplete":true,"message":"Technical design is complete. I researched existing agents and actions, consulted the Database Research Agent for entity schemas, and designed the optimal solution. The design reuses Database Research Agent for reads and uses minimal targeted actions.","payloadChangeRequest":{"updateElements":{"TechnicalDesign":"# Customer Feedback Analyzer – Technical Design\n\n## Overview\n\n**Agent Name**: Customer Feedback Analyzer  \n**Agent Type**: Loop  \n**Description**: Analyzes customer feedback from database, performs sentiment analysis, and generates weekly email reports with actionable insights  \n**Icon**: fa-solid fa-chart-line  \n**DefaultArtifactTypeID**: null (orchestration agent, no direct artifact output)\n\n## Agent Architecture\n\nThis is a Loop-type orchestrator that coordinates database research, text analysis, and email delivery. It uses existing sub-agents for specialized tasks rather than duplicating functionality with actions.\n\n```mermaid\ngraph TD\n  Parent[Customer Feedback Analyzer] -.->|related| DBAgent[Database Research Agent]\n  Parent --> TextAction[Action: Text Analyzer]\n  Parent --> SendAction[Action: Send Single Message]\n  style Parent fill:#1E293B,color:#fff\n  style DBAgent fill:#10B981,color:#fff\n  style TextAction fill:#3B82F6,color:#fff\n  style SendAction fill:#3B82F6,color:#fff\n```\n\n## Research Results\n\n### Available Sub-Agents (from Find Candidate Agents)\n\n**Database Research Agent** (ID: 5ddf4f5d-b977-42b0-bed5-4a2f0021bc58)\n- Can query CustomerFeedback entity\n- Returns structured data with all fields including ID, FeedbackText, Rating, Category, CreatedAt\n- Supports date range filtering\n\n### Available Actions (from Find Candidate Actions)\n\n**Text Analyzer** (ID: 82169F64-8566-4AE7-9C87-190A885C98A9)\n- Performs sentiment analysis and theme extraction\n- Input: text content\n- Output: sentiment (positive/negative/neutral), themes, confidence scores\n\n**Send Single Message** (ID: A3B4C5D6-E7F8-9A0B-1C2D-3E4F5A6B7C8D)\n- Sends emails via SendGrid or Microsoft Graph\n- Required params: Provider (''SendGrid''), MessageType (''Email''), Subject, Body, To, From\n\n### Database Schema (from Database Research Agent)\n\n**Entity**: CustomerFeedback  \n**Primary Key**: ID (UUID)  \n**Fields**:\n- ID: UUID (primary key)\n- FeedbackText: TEXT\n- Rating: INTEGER (1-5)\n- Category: VARCHAR(100)\n- CustomerID: UUID\n- CreatedAt: datetime\n- UpdatedAt: datetime\n\n## Related Sub-Agents\n\n### Database Research Agent\n- **Type**: related\n- **Existing Agent ID**: 5ddf4f5d-b977-42b0-bed5-4a2f0021bc58\n- **Purpose**: Query CustomerFeedback table for past week''s data\n- **Input Mapping**: {\"*\": \"query\"}\n- **Output Mapping**: {\"*\": \"feedbackData\"}\n- **Context Paths**: [\"*\"]\n\n## Actions\n\n### Text Analyzer\n- **ID**: 82169F64-8566-4AE7-9C87-190A885C98A9\n- **Purpose**: Analyze sentiment and extract themes from feedback text\n- **When Used**: After collecting feedback data, analyze each feedback item\n\n### Send Single Message\n- **ID**: A3B4C5D6-E7F8-9A0B-1C2D-3E4F5A6B7C8D\n- **Purpose**: Email the weekly report to stakeholders\n- **When Used**: After completing analysis and generating report summary\n\n## Main Agent Prompt\n\n```\n# Customer Feedback Analyzer\n\nYou orchestrate weekly customer feedback analysis and reporting.\n\n## Your Workflow\n\n### Step 1: Collect Feedback Data\nCall Database Research Agent with: \"Find CustomerFeedback records from the past 7 days. Return JSON with all columns. Include ID, FeedbackText, Rating, Category, CustomerID, CreatedAt.\"\n\n### Step 2: Analyze Each Feedback Item\nFor each feedback item call Text Analyzer with FeedbackText. Extract sentiment and themes.\n\n### Step 3: Aggregate Insights\nCalculate total count, sentiment breakdown, average rating, top 10 themes, critical issues (Rating ≤ 2 AND negative).\n\n### Step 4: Send Report\nCall Send Single Message:\n- Provider: ''SendGrid''\n- MessageType: ''Email''\n- Subject: \"Weekly Customer Feedback Report - [Date]\"\n- Body: [HTML report]\n- To: \"product@company.com,support@company.com\"\n```\n\n## Payload Structure\n\n### Input\n```json\n{\n  \"dateRangeStart\": \"2025-10-22T00:00:00Z\",\n  \"dateRangeEnd\": \"2025-10-29T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n### Output\n```json\n{\n  \"feedbackData\": [...],\n  \"analysis\": [...],\n  \"report\": { \"totalCount\": 1234, \"sentimentBreakdown\": {\"positive\": 60, \"neutral\": 30, \"negative\": 10} },\n  \"emailSent\": true\n}\n```\n\n## Why This Design is Optimal\n\n✅ Reuses Database Research Agent for READ operations  \n✅ Uses Text Analyzer for sentiment analysis  \n✅ Database entity/fields verified via Database Research Agent  \n✅ Minimal actions — no redundancy  \n✅ Clear prompt delegation"}}},"example_1b_creation_mode_with_schema_changes":{"description":"Planning Designer when the agent needs a new database table that doesn''t exist yet. Writes pendingSchemaChanges to payload (machine-readable, Agent Manager passes to DB Designer post-approval) AND includes a ## Planned Schema Changes section in TechnicalDesign (human-readable, shown to user). Does NOT call Database Designer directly.","taskComplete":true,"message":"Technical design is complete. No existing entity was found for vacation request tracking, so I''ve defined a new table specification in pendingSchemaChanges. Agent Manager will create it after user approval, then Architect will wire up the agent.","payloadChangeRequest":{"updateElements":{"pendingSchemaChanges":[{"name":"Vacation Requests","description":"Stores vacation request records submitted by employees. Each row is a single request with start/end dates, status, and a reference to the employee who submitted it.","schemaName":"__mj_UDT","modificationType":"create","columns":[{"name":"EmployeeID","type":UUID,"description":"References the User who submitted this vacation request","required":true,"foreignKeyTarget":"__mj."User"."ID""},{"name":"StartDate","type":"DATE","description":"First day of the requested vacation","required":true},{"name":"EndDate","type":"DATE","description":"Last day of the requested vacation","required":true},{"name":"Status","type":"VARCHAR(50)","description":"Lifecycle status of the request: Pending, Approved, Rejected, Cancelled","required":true},{"name":"Notes","type":TEXT,"description":"Optional notes from the employee about the request","required":false},{"name":"ReviewedByID","type":UUID,"description":"References the User (manager) who approved or rejected the request. Null until reviewed.","required":false,"foreignKeyTarget":"__mj."User"."ID""},{"name":"ReviewedAt","type":"DATETIMEOFFSET","description":"Timestamp when the request was approved or rejected","required":false}]}],"TechnicalDesign":"# Vacation Request Agent – Technical Design\n\n## Overview\n\n**Agent Name**: Vacation Request Agent\n**Agent Type**: Loop\n**Description**: Allows employees to submit vacation requests and notifies their manager for approval.\n\n## Planned Schema Changes\n\nThe following database entity will be **created** automatically after you approve the design.\n\n### New Entity: Vacation Requests (schema: __mj_UDT)\nStores vacation request records submitted by employees.\n\n| Column | Type | Required | Notes |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| EmployeeID | UUID | Yes | FK → User."ID" |\n| StartDate | DATE | Yes | First day of vacation |\n| EndDate | DATE | Yes | Last day of vacation |\n| Status | VARCHAR(50) | Yes | Pending, Approved, Rejected, Cancelled |\n| Notes | TEXT | No | Optional employee notes |\n| ReviewedByID | UUID | No | FK → User."ID" (manager who reviewed) |\n| ReviewedAt | DATETIMEOFFSET | No | When the request was reviewed |\n\n## Agent Architecture\n\nThis is a Loop-type agent that handles vacation request submission and approval notification.\n\n## Actions\n\n### Create Record\n- **Purpose**: Save a new vacation request to the Vacation Requests entity\n- **When Used**: When employee submits a request\n\n### Update Record\n- **Purpose**: Update Status and ReviewedByID/ReviewedAt when manager approves or rejects\n- **When Used**: When manager responds\n\n### Send Single Message\n- **Purpose**: Email manager when a new request is submitted; email employee when request is reviewed\n\n## Main Agent Prompt\n\nYou handle vacation request submissions and approvals.\n\n### Submitting a Request\nCall Create Record with EntityName=''Vacation Requests'' and Fields: { EmployeeID, StartDate, EndDate, Status: ''Pending'', Notes }\nThen call Send Single Message to notify the employee''s manager.\n\n### Approving / Rejecting\nCall Update Record with EntityName=''Vacation Requests'', PrimaryKey: { ID: <request-id> }, Fields: { Status: ''Approved'' | ''Rejected'', ReviewedByID, ReviewedAt }\nThen call Send Single Message to notify the employee."}}},"example_2_modification_mode":{"taskComplete":true,"message":"Modification plan is complete. I researched the existing agent, identified the targeted change needed, and verified the database entity exists. The plan adds one action and one prompt step with minimal impact to the existing workflow.","payloadChangeRequest":{"updateElements":{"modificationPlan":"# Modification Plan for Customer Feedback Analyzer\n\n## Current State\n\n**Agent Type**: Loop  \n**Current Actions**: Text Analyzer, Send Single Message  \n**Current Sub-Agents**: Database Research Agent\n\n## User Request\n\n\"Add the ability to save the analysis results back to the database so we can track trends over time.\"\n\n## Research Findings\n\n### Available Actions (from Find Candidate Actions)\n\n**Create Record** (ID: 7C8D9E0F-1A2B-3C4D-5E6F-7A8B9C0D1E2F)\n- Creates new database records\n- Params: EntityName (string), Fields (object with field:value pairs)\n- Returns: PrimaryKey (object with created record ID)\n\n### Database Schema (from Database Research Agent)\n\n**Existing Entity**: FeedbackAnalysis  \n**Fields**: ID, AnalysisDate, FeedbackCount, PositivePercent, NegativePercent, NeutralPercent, AverageRating, TopThemes, CriticalIssueCount\n\n## Recommended Changes\n\n### Add Action: Create Record\n- **Action ID**: 7C8D9E0F-1A2B-3C4D-5E6F-7A8B9C0D1E2F\n- **Why**: Enables saving analysis results to FeedbackAnalysis table\n\n### Update Main Agent Prompt\n\nAdd Step 4.5 (between analysis aggregation and email sending):\n```\n### Step 4.5: Save Analysis to Database\nCall Create Record:\n- EntityName: \"FeedbackAnalysis\"\n- Fields: { AnalysisDate, FeedbackCount, PositivePercent, NegativePercent, NeutralPercent, AverageRating, TopThemes, CriticalIssueCount }\n```\n\n## Validation\n\n✅ No redundant actions  \n✅ Action ID from actual Find Candidate Actions results  \n✅ Database entity verified via Database Research Agent  \n✅ Minimal impact — adds one action, one prompt step"}}}}';
  p_ValidationBehavior_ec79d5fa := 'Strict';
  p_MaxRetries_ec79d5fa := 2;
  p_RetryDelayMS_ec79d5fa := 1000;
